12/05/2005
BUCHAREST, Romania -- EU Enlargement Commissioner Olli Rehn met on Wednesday (11 May) with Romanian Prime Minister Calin Popescu Tariceanu to discuss EU accession-related reforms in the country, ahead of parliament's ratification of the EU Accession Treaty next week. 
Rehn was in Bucharest to attend the South-East European Co-operation Process summit.
Also Wednesday, a two-day drill simulating the response to a nuclear disaster began at Romania's Cernavoda nuclear power plant. 
It is a joint project involving Romanian authorities, the International Atomic Energy Association and the European Commission. 
(Sega - 12/05/05; Rompres, EU Web site, EU Observer, Reuters - 11/05/05)
